<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
A study of the penis valves of the three syntypes of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. cothurnatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="cothurnatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. cothurnatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed that two of them belong to 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. germanicus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="germanicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. germanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including the specimen here designated as the lectotype, and one to 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. aericeps" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="aericeps">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. aericeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These old specimens all have rather pale wings, but probably they have faded: 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. germanicus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="germanicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. germanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. junci" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="junci">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. junci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus cothurnatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cothurnatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus cothurnatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
auct.] typically have darker wings. The specimen labelled by Haris as lectotype is designated here as a lectotype for 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. cothurnatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="cothurnatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. cothurnatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Serville and 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. cothurnatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="cothurnatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. cothurnatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is regarded as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. germanicus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="germanicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. germanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see above, under 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus cothurnatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cothurnatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus cothurnatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
auct. nec Serville, 1823).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1835" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dosytheus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dosytheus fuscipennis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dosytheus fuscipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Stephens, 1835. Lectotype ♀. Labelled: &quot;Type H.T. [holotype]&quot; [round with a red margin, printed], &quot;B.M. TYPE HYM. [printed] 1.578.&quot;, &quot;B.M. TYPE HYM. [printed] 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1835" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dosytheus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dosytheus fuscipennis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dosytheus fuscipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Stephens, JF" journalOrPublisher="Baldwin and Cradock, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="1 - 312" refId="B169" refString="Stephens, JF, 1835. Illustrations of British Entomology; or, a Synopsis of Indigenous Insects: Containing their generic and specific distinctions; with an account of their metamorphosis, times of appearance, localities, food, and economy, as far as practicable. Mandibulata. Baldwin and Cradock, London 7: 1 - 312" title="Illustrations of British Entomology; or, a Synopsis of Indigenous Insects: Containing their generic and specific distinctions; with an account of their metamorphosis, times of appearance, localities, food, and economy, as far as practicable. Mandibulata." volume="7" year="1835">Stephens 1835</bibRefCitation>
.&quot;, &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">fuscipennis</emphasis>
.&quot;, &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1801" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus pratensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pratensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus pratensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, L.&quot; [printed], &quot;Stephens Coll. 53-46&quot; [printed], &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1801" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus germanicus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="germanicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus germanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fabricius) M.Heidemaa det.&quot; [printed]. Condition good, legs partly destroyed. BMNH.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
The number of specimens was not given by Stephens. The species description should therefore be assumed to have been based on syntypes. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirby, WF" journalOrPublisher="Trustees of the Museum, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B74" refString="Kirby, WF, 1882. List of Hymenoptera with Descriptions and Figures of the Typical Specimens in the British Museum. 1. Tenthredinidae and Siricidae. Trustees of the Museum, London" title="List of Hymenoptera with Descriptions and Figures of the Typical Specimens in the British Museum. 1. Tenthredinidae and Siricidae." year="1882">Kirby (1882)</bibRefCitation>
referred to the &quot;♀. (Type of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. fuscipennis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. fuscipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.) S. Scotland. J. F. Stephens&quot;, and according to the labels and the collection catalogue this was the only specimen from the Stephens collection in the BMNH. The specimen fits the original description, and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kirby’s">Kirby's</normalizedToken>
statement qualifies as a valid lectotype designation, because there is no evidence in the original description that more than one type specimen existed (
<bibRefCitation author="Hellen, W" journalOrPublisher="Notulae Entomologicae" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B68" refString="ICZN (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth Edition.International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." year="1948">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
Article 74.6.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dosytheus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dosytheus hyalinalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyalinalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dosytheus hyalinalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Stephens, 1835. Lectotype ♀ hereby designated, labelled: &quot;B.M. TYPE HYM [printed] 1.577.&quot;, &quot;B.M. TYPE HYM [printed] 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dosytheus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dosytheus hyalinalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyalinalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dosytheus hyalinalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (
<bibRefCitation author="Stephens, JF" journalOrPublisher="Baldwin and Cradock, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="1 - 312" refId="B169" refString="Stephens, JF, 1835. Illustrations of British Entomology; or, a Synopsis of Indigenous Insects: Containing their generic and specific distinctions; with an account of their metamorphosis, times of appearance, localities, food, and economy, as far as practicable. Mandibulata. Baldwin and Cradock, London 7: 1 - 312" title="Illustrations of British Entomology; or, a Synopsis of Indigenous Insects: Containing their generic and specific distinctions; with an account of their metamorphosis, times of appearance, localities, food, and economy, as far as practicable. Mandibulata." volume="7" year="1835">Stephens 1835</bibRefCitation>
)&quot;, &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dosytheus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dosytheus hyalinalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyalinalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dosytheus hyalinalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Steph&quot;, &quot;42 1b&quot; [round], &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1801" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus pratensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pratensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus pratensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, L.&quot; [printed], &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1801" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus germanicus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="germanicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus germanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(F.) M.Heidemaa det.&quot; [printed]. BMNH.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
In the original description Stephens indicates that he had more than one specimen, because he gives color characters for both sexes. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kirby’s">Kirby's</normalizedToken>
statement &quot;♀ Type of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. hyalinalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="hyalinalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. hyalinalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="Kirby, WF" journalOrPublisher="Trustees of the Museum, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B74" refString="Kirby, WF, 1882. List of Hymenoptera with Descriptions and Figures of the Typical Specimens in the British Museum. 1. Tenthredinidae and Siricidae. Trustees of the Museum, London" title="List of Hymenoptera with Descriptions and Figures of the Typical Specimens in the British Museum. 1. Tenthredinidae and Siricidae." year="1882">Kirby 1882</bibRefCitation>
) refers to the only syntype from the Stephens collection that was present in the BMNH, but cannot be accepted as a lectotype designation, because it is clear that Stephens based his description on more than one specimen (
<bibRefCitation author="Hellen, W" journalOrPublisher="Notulae Entomologicae" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B68" refString="ICZN (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth Edition.International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." year="1948">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
Article 74.5.). The synonymy with 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. pratensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="pratensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. pratensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on a misidentification, was adopted for example by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.10348" author="de Dalla Torre, CG" journalOrPublisher="Berling, Lund" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B37" refString="de Dalla Torre, CG, 1894. Catalogus Hymenopterorum hucusque descriptorum systematicus et synonymicus. Vol. 1: Tenthredinidae incl. Uroceridae (Phyllophaga &amp; Xylophaga). Guilelmus Engelmann, Lipsiae, [[6] pp.+ pp. I-VIII +] 1-459. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.10348" title="Catalogus Hymenopterorum hucusque descriptorum systematicus et synonymicus. Vol. 1: Tenthredinidae incl. Uroceridae (Phyllophaga &amp; Xylophaga). Guilelmus Engelmann, Lipsiae, [[ 6] pp. + pp. I-VIII +] 1 - 459." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.10348" year="1894">de Dalla Torre (1894)</bibRefCitation>
and most other subsequent works.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1835" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dosytheus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dosytheus xanthopus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthopus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dosytheus xanthopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Stephens, 1835. The only specimen found in the collection (BMNH) labelled as &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1835" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dosytheus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dosytheus xanthopus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthopus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dosytheus xanthopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; and &quot;B.M. TYPE 1.257.&quot; belongs to 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. germanicus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="germanicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. germanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It cannot be a syntype of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. xanthopus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="xanthopus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. xanthopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because the specimen disagrees with the original description: its mesoscutellum is orange, not black as described, and the locality label (&quot;Kent, Darenth, J. F. Stephens BM 1853 - 42&quot;, probably added by Benson) does not match the locality given by Stephens. Interestingly, it was labelled by Benson (handwritten): &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1801" baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1818" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus etruscus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="etruscus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus etruscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
?&quot;.
</paragraph>
